# Biasbuster Project Structure

Biasbuster is an AI-powered tool for detecting bias in media content. The project is organized into several key directories:

- **web-platform/** - Frontend web application with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
  - Main entry point is [web-platform/index.html](mdc:web-platform/index.html)
  - Core functionality in [web-platform/script.js](mdc:web-platform/script.js)
  - Styling in [web-platform/style.css](mdc:web-platform/style.css)
  
- **src/** - Backend server and API components
  - Server configuration in [src/config](mdc:src/config)
  - API controllers in [src/controllers](mdc:src/controllers)
  - API routes in [src/routes](mdc:src/routes)
  - Data models in [src/models](mdc:src/models)
  - Service layer in [src/services](mdc:src/services)
  
- **chrome-extension/** - Browser extension for direct webpage analysis
  
- **docs/** - Documentation and requirements

- **prompts/** - AI prompt templates for bias analysis

- **scripts/** - Utility scripts for development and deployment
